Example
Encode a string in base-64:

Copy
let str = "Hello World!";
let enc = window.btoa(str);
let res = "Encoded String: " + enc;

Description
The btoa() method encodes a string in base-64.

This method uses the "A-Z", "a-z", "0-9", "+", "/" and "=" characters to encode the string.

We can use the atob() method to decode a base-64 encoded string.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
btoa()	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Copy
window.btoa(str)
Parameter Values
Parameter
str
Type/Optional
Required.
Description
The string to be encoded
Return Value
A String, representing the base-64 encoded string
